<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Isaiah 15:1-9</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="66">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="9">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">The pronouncement against Mo&acute;ab: Because in the night it has been despoiled, Ar of Mo&acute;ab itself has been silenced. Because in the night it has been despoiled, Kir of Mo&acute;ab itself has been silenced.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">He has gone up to The House and to Di&acute;bon, to the high places, to a weeping. Over Ne&acute;bo and over Med&acute;e&middot;ba Mo&acute;ab itself howls. On all heads in it there is baldness; every beard is clipped.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">In its streets they have girded on sackcloth. Upon the roofs thereof and in the public squares thereof everyone thereof howls, going down with weeping.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And Hesh&acute;bon and E&middot;le&middot;a&acute;leh cry out. As far as Ja&acute;haz their voice has been heard. That is why the armed men of Mo&acute;ab themselves keep shouting. His very soul has quivered within him.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">My own heart cries out over Mo&acute;ab himself. The runaways thereof are as far along as Zo&acute;ar [and] Eg&acute;lath-she&middot;li&acute;shi&middot;yah. For on the ascent of Lu&acute;hith—with weeping [each] one goes up on it; for on the way to Hor&middot;o&middot;na&acute;im they arouse the outcry about the catastrophe.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">For the very waters of Nim&acute;rim become sheer desolations. For the green grass has dried up, the grass has come to an end; nothing has become green.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">That is why the leftovers and their stored goods that they have put up, they keep carrying them away right over the torrent valley of the poplars.</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">For the outcry has gone around the territory of Mo&acute;ab. The howling thereof is clear to Eg&middot;la&acute;im; the howling thereof is clear to Be&acute;er-e&acute;lim,</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">because the very waters of Di&acute;mon have become full of blood. For upon Di&acute;mon I shall place additional things, such as a lion for the escapees of Mo&acute;ab who escape and for the remaining ones of the ground.</span>
</p>
</form>

