<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Isaiah 20:1-6</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="66">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="6">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">In the year that Tar&acute;tan came to Ash&acute;dod, when Sar&acute;gon the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a sent him, and he proceeded to war against Ash&acute;dod and to capture it;</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">at that time Jehovah spoke by the hand of Isaiah the son of A&acute;moz, saying: “Go, and you must loosen the sackcloth from off your hips; and your sandals you should draw from off your feet.” And he proceeded to do so, walking about naked and barefoot.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And Jehovah went on to say: “Just as my servant Isaiah has walked about naked and barefoot three years as a sign and a portent against Egypt and against E&middot;thi&middot;o&acute;pi&middot;a,</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">so the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a will lead the body of captives of Egypt and the exiles of E&middot;thi&middot;o&acute;pi&middot;a, boys and old men, naked and barefoot, and with buttocks stripped, the nakedness of Egypt.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And they will certainly be terrified and be ashamed of E&middot;thi&middot;o&acute;pi&middot;a their looked-for hope and of Egypt their beauty.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And the inhabitant of this coastland will be certain to say in that day, ‘There is how our looked-for hope is, to which we fled for assistance, in order to be delivered because of the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a! And how shall we ourselves escape?’”</span>
</p>
</form>

