<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">Isaiah 37:1-38</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="66">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="38">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about that as soon as King Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah heard, he immediately ripped his garments apart and covered himself with sackcloth and came into the house of Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Further, he sent E&middot;li&acute;a&middot;kim, who was over the household, and Sheb&acute;na the secretary and the older men of the priests covered with sackcloth to Isaiah the son of A&acute;moz the prophet.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And they proceeded to say to him: “This is what Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah has said, ‘This day is a day of distress and of rebuke and of scornful insolence, for the sons have come as far as the womb’s mouth, and there is no power to give birth.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Perhaps Jehovah your God will hear the words of Rab&acute;sha&middot;keh, whom the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a his lord sent to taunt the living God, and he will actually call him to account for the words that Jehovah your God has heard. And you must lift up prayer in behalf of the remnant that are to be found.’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">So the servants of King Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah came in to Isaiah.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">Then Isaiah said to them: “This is what <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> should say to <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> lord, ‘This is what Jehovah has said: “Do not be afraid because of the words that you have heard with which the attendants of the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a spoke abusively of me.</span> <a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">Here I am putting a spirit in him, and he must hear a report and return to his own land; and I shall certainly cause him to fall by the sword in his own land.”’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">After that Rab&acute;sha&middot;keh returned and found the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a fighting against Lib&acute;nah, for he had heard that he had pulled away from La&acute;chish.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">Now he heard it said concerning Tir&middot;ha&acute;kah the king of E&middot;thi&middot;o&acute;pi&middot;a: “He has come out to fight against you.” When he heard, he at once sent messengers to Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah, saying:</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">“This is what <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men should say to Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah the king of Judah, ‘Do not let your God in whom you are trusting deceive you, saying: “Jerusalem will not be given into the hand of the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a.”</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">Look! You yourself have heard what the kings of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a did to all the lands by devoting them to destruction, and will you yourself be delivered?</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">Have the gods of the nations that my forefathers brought to ruin delivered them, even Go&acute;zan and Ha&acute;ran and Re&acute;zeph and the sons of E&acute;den that were in Tel-as&acute;sar?</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Where is the king of Ha&acute;math and the king of Ar&acute;pad and the king of the city of Seph&middot;ar&middot;va&acute;im—of He&acute;na and of Iv&acute;vah?’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">Then Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah took the letters out of the hand of the messengers and read them, after which Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah went up to the house of Jehovah and spread it out before Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah began to pray to Jehovah, saying:</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">“O Jehovah of armies, the God of Israel, sitting upon the cherubs, you alone are the [true] God of all the kingdoms of the earth. You yourself have made the heavens and the earth.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Incline your ear, O Jehovah, and hear. Open your eyes, O Jehovah, and see, and hear all the words of Sen&middot;nach&acute;er&middot;ib that he has sent to taunt the living God.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">It is a fact, O Jehovah, that the kings of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a have devastated all the lands, and their own land.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And there was a consigning of their gods to the fire, because they were no gods, but the workmanship of man’s hands, wood and stone, so that they destroyed them.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And now, O Jehovah our God, save us out of his hand, that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you, O Jehovah, are [God] alone.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And Isaiah the son of A&acute;moz proceeded to send to Hez&middot;e&middot;ki&acute;ah, saying: “This is what Jehovah the God of Israel has said, ‘Because you have prayed to me concerning Sen&middot;nach&acute;er&middot;ib the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a,</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">this is the word that Jehovah has spoken against him:</span>
</p>

<p class="p"> 
       <span id="vs22-2">“The virgin daughter of Zion has despised you, she has held you in derision.<br><span class="z">Behind you the daughter of Jerusalem has wagged [her] head.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Whom have you taunted and spoken of abusively?<br><span class="z">And against whom have you lifted up [your] voice</span><br><span class="p">And do you raise your eyes on high?</span><br><span class="z">It is against the Holy One of Israel!</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">By means of your servants you have taunted Jehovah and you say,<br><span class="z">‘With the multitude of my war chariots I myself—</span><br><span class="p">I shall certainly ascend the height of mountainous regions,</span><br><span class="z">The remotest parts of Leb&acute;a&middot;non;</span><br><span class="p">And I shall cut down its lofty cedars, its choice juniper trees.</span><br><span class="z">And I shall enter its final height, the forest of its orchard.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">I myself shall certainly dig and drink waters,<br><span class="z">And I shall dry up with the soles of my feet all the Nile canals of Egypt.’</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Have you not heard? From remote times it is what I will do.<br><span class="z">From bygone days I have even formed it. Now I will bring it in.</span><br><span class="z">And you will serve to make fortified cities become desolate as piles of ruins.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And their inhabitants will be feeble-handed;<br><span class="z">They will simply be terrified and ashamed.</span><br><span class="p">They must become as vegetation of the field and green tender grass,</span><br><span class="z">Grass of the roofs and of the terrace before the east wind.</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And your sitting quiet and your going out and your coming in I well know,<br><span class="z">And your exciting yourself against me,</span></span>
</p>

<p class="l"><a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Because your exciting yourself against me and your roaring have come up into my ears.<br><span class="z">And I shall certainly put my hook in your nose and my bridle between your lips,</span><br><span class="z">And I shall indeed lead you back by the way by which you have come.”</span></span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">“‘And this will be the sign for you: There will be an eating this year of the growth from spilled kernels, and in the second year grain that shoots up of itself; but in the third year sow seed, <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> people, and reap, and plant vineyards and eat their fruitage.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">And those who escape of the house of Judah, those who are left remaining, will certainly take root downward and produce fruitage upward.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">For out of Jerusalem a remnant will go forth and those who escape out of Mount Zion. The very zeal of Jehovah of armies will do this.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">“‘Therefore this is what Jehovah has said concerning the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a: “He will not come into this city, nor will he shoot an arrow there, nor confront it with a shield, nor cast up a siege rampart against it.”’</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">“‘By the way by which he came he will return, and into this city he will not come,’ is the utterance of Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">‘And I shall certainly defend this city to save it for my own sake and for the sake of David my servant.’”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And the angel of Jehovah proceeded to go forth and strike down a hundred and eighty-five thousand in the camp of the As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;ans. When people rose up early in the morning, why, there all of them were dead carcasses.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Hence Sen&middot;nach&acute;er&middot;ib the king of As&middot;syr&acute;i&middot;a pulled away and went and returned and took up dwelling in Nin&acute;e&middot;veh.</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">And it came about that as he was bowing down at the house of Nis&acute;roch his god, A&middot;dram&acute;me&middot;lech and Shar&middot;e&acute;zer, his own sons, struck him down with the sword, and they themselves escaped to the land of Ar&acute;a&middot;rat. And E&acute;sar-had&acute;don his son began to reign in place of him.</span>
</p>
</form>

<script language="JavaScript1.2" type="text/javascript">
